<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1143">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111W74/121/2</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BGW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Buckner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-04">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1914</hi>.</date>[<hi rend="italic">Received October 9</hi>.] </dateline>
                        <p rend="flushleft">No. 59]</p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s telegrams
                            on the subject of neutrality of wireless stations in Liberia, I have the
                            honor to report that the Liberian Government has met the situation here
                            by closing both the German and French stations. I understand this was
                            done by mutual consent on the part of the management of each
                            station.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">George W. Buckner</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>